  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0f3a2c8c7b8f4d9c9d5a3d11d5f50101, type: 3}
  m_Name: PokedexToad
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entryId: toad
  commonName: American Toad
  scientificName: Anaxyrus americanus
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 1007e734ad59ade4ca34eefaf66f412a, type: 3}
  category: Amphibian
  habitat: Forests
  height: 5 - 11 cm
  weight: 20 - 55 g
  diet: Insectivore
  rarity: Common
  shortDescription: A stout, nocturnal amphibian covered in wart-like glands, perfectly
    camouflaged to blend into the muddy forest floor.
  behaviorNotes: Mainly active at night or on rainy days. It moves by making short,
    hopping movements rather than long leaps and burrows backwards into the soil
    to sleep during the day.
  observationTips: Scan the ground near decaying logs, damp rocks, or dense leaf
    litter. Listen for a long, musical, high-pitched trill lasting up to 30 seconds,
    which males use to call out near shallow pools.
  funFact: The "warts" on their skin do not cause warts on humans, but they do secrete
    a milky, toxic fluid called bufonin that tastes terrible to predators and can
    make animals that try to eat them very sick.
  facts:
  - While they are amphibians, their thick, warty skin allows them to live far away
    from bodies of water compared to typical frogs.
  - They can catch prey in less than a fraction of a second by flicking out a sticky
    tongue attached to the front of their mouth.
  - To survive freezing winter temperatures, they use their hind legs to dig backwards
    deep into the soil below the frost line.
